{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592420","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592420"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:14:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:14:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15236"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15236","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15236"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.31,0.38,0.27,0.04,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7927"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65155"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7927","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7927"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15236"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50592"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8743"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19313"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19316"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21649"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65155","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65155"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA patient presents with laboratory evidence of folate deficiency.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following regions of the gastrointestinal tract is the primary site of folate absorption?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Duodenum","Jejunum","Ileum","Descending colon","Rectum"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFolate deficiency can result from inadequate dietary intake, malabsorption (especially in jejunal disease), increased requirements, or certain medications that interfere with folate metabolism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFolate absorption occurs primarily in the \u003Cstrong\u003Ejejunum\u003C/strong\u003E through carrier-mediated transport. Before absorption can occur, dietary folate (polyglutamate) must be converted to the monoglutamate form by intestinal conjugase enzymes in the brush border.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eduodenum\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily responsible for iron absorption and some mineral absorption. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eileum\u003C/strong\u003E is the main site for vitamin B12 and bile acid absorption. The \u003Cstrong\u003Edescending colon\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Erectum\u003C/strong\u003E are not significant sites of nutrient absorption, instead being primarily involved in water reabsorption and stool storage respectively.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Folate is primarily absorbed in the proximal jejunum through carrier-mediated transport.","Dietary folate must first be converted to monoglutamate form by intestinal conjugase before absorption can occur."],"references":["Milman N. Intestinal absorption of folic acid - new physiologic \u0026 molecular aspects. Indian J Med Res. 2012 Nov;136(5):725-8. PMID: 23287118; PMCID: PMC3573592","Thomson AB, Keelan M, Thiesen A, Clandinin MT, Ropeleski M, Wild GE. Small bowel review: diseases of the small intestine. Dig Dis Sci. 2001 Dec;46(12):2555-66. doi: 10.1023/a:1012782321827. PMID: 11768246","Gu\u00e9ant JL, Gu\u00e9ant-Rodriguez RM, Alpers DH. Vitamin B12 absorption and malabsorption. Vitam Horm. 2022;119:241-274. doi: 10.1016/bs.vh.2022.01.016. Epub 2022 Mar 1. PMID: 35337622","Basile EJ, Launico MV, Sheer AJ. Physiology, Nutrient Absorption. [Updated 2023 Oct 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishi